[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ryan Bertrand: Southampton and England defender signs new five-year deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Southampton and England defender Ryan Bertrand has signed a new five-year contract with the Premier League club.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Bertrand, 26, joined Saints from Chelsea for Â£10m in February 2015 following an initial loan spell.
The left-back has won nine caps for England, most recently against Slovakia in the group stage at Euro 2016.
Bertrand joins team-mates Virgil van Dijk, Fraser Forster, James Ward-Prowse and Steven Davis in agreeing a new deal with Southampton this summer.
